com.jbion.utils.xml.serialization.parameters

Class ParamsSchema

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.jbion.utils.xml.serialization.parameters.ParamsSchema

  • public class ParamsSchema
extends Object
    Describes a schema of parameters needed by a program.

    Each parameter has a unique name (a key) to be referred to, and can be required or optional. When optional, a default value must be provided. One can also specify a short description for each parameter.

    Each parameter is associated to a Serializer, which also indicates its class.

    Author:
    Joffrey Bion

      • isSuperSetOf

        public boolean isSuperSetOf(ParamsSchema otherSchema)
        Returns true if all the specifications defined in the given ParamsSchema exist in this parameters schema, and if they are all identical as defined by ParamSpec.equals(Object).
        Parameters:
        otherSchema - The whole schema to add.
        Returns:
        true if all the specifications defined in the given ParamsSchema exist in this parameters schema, and if they are all identical as defined by ParamSpec.equals(Object).
        false if at least one ParamSpec is absent from this schema.
        false if at least one ParamSpec appears with the same key in this schema and otherSchema but is not the same as defined by ParamSpec.equals(Object).
